bukkitrunnablehelper.interfaces

Interface Plannable

  • All Superinterfaces:
    TimeOutable
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    TimedRepeatable

    public interface Plannable
extends TimeOutable
    If a class implements this interface, it is a Plannable. Meaning that it can be timed out after a specified amount of ticks. A Plannable has a timeout method which specifies what will happen when it is timed out, and a getTimeOutTicks method wchich specifies after how many ticks this Plannable will be timed out.

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      int getTimeOutTicks()
      Gets the total amount of ticks that this Plannable will last.
